<vulnerability_guide>
  <title>CERTIFICATE PINNING BYPASS</title>

  <critical>Certificate pinning ties an application to specific certificates or public keys, preventing MITM attacks even with compromised CAs. Bypassing pinning allows traffic interception, credential theft, and API reverse engineering. Mobile apps and thick clients are primary targets.</critical>

  <scope>
    - Android certificate pinning bypass
    - iOS certificate pinning bypass
    - Desktop application bypasses
    - SSL/TLS interception setup
    - Frida and hooking techniques
    - Network Security Config attacks
  </scope>

